stylometry: A simulation model is useful because it takes several different possible inputs and uses it to simulate a simulation (1000 interrations) in order to receive a desired output. This is useful because simulation models can find the best solution or give the user to see the possible inputs and resulting outputs so that he/she can make the best decision. I would use simulation in a business situation in which I am trying to figure out when to release a product. If I have a probability distribution of possible demands at different times I can simulate how well a product will do at different times and therefore decide when would be most profitable.
